5ï¸âƒ£ How does an end-user request reach an application?
ğŸ“Œ Stages involved:
1ï¸âƒ£ User makes a request from a browser (https://myapp.com).
2ï¸âƒ£ DNS Resolution â†’ Resolves myapp.com to an IP address.
3ï¸âƒ£ Load Balancer (ALB/NLB) â†’ Routes traffic to the right server.
4ï¸âƒ£ Firewall/Security Group Check â†’ Allows valid requests.
5ï¸âƒ£ Application Server (EC2/K8s/ECS) â†’ Handles the request.
6ï¸âƒ£ Database Interaction (if needed) â†’ Retrieves data from RDS/DynamoDB.
7ï¸âƒ£ Response Sent Back â†’ User sees the webpage.

6ï¸âƒ£ What is the difference between Observability and Monitoring?
Feature	Monitoring	Observability
Purpose	Detect known issues	Discover unknown issues
Data Type	Metrics & logs	Logs, metrics, traces
Example	Checking CPU usage	Debugging why a service failed
Tools	Prometheus, Grafana	OpenTelemetry, Datadog
7ï¸âƒ£ How can you secure a CI/CD pipeline?
âœ… Use IAM roles & least privilege access.
âœ… Enable secret management (e.g., AWS Secrets Manager, HashiCorp Vault).
âœ… Code scanning â†’ Use tools like SonarQube, Snyk for vulnerability detection.
âœ… Restrict direct production access (manual approvals for critical changes).
âœ… Use signed artifacts & checksum validation.

8ï¸âƒ£ Do you have hands-on experience with Terraform workspaces, and what does it mean?
âœ… Terraform Workspaces allow managing multiple environments (Dev, Staging, Prod) in the same codebase.
ğŸ“Œ Example:

terraform workspace new dev â†’ Creates a Dev workspace
terraform workspace new prod â†’ Creates a Prod workspace
terraform workspace select dev â†’ Switch to Dev workspace
ğŸ’¡ Benefit: No need to manage separate Terraform directories for different environments.

9ï¸âƒ£ In AWS, how to configure an S3 bucket as a backend in Terraform and implement state locking?
ğŸ“Œ Steps:
1ï¸âƒ£ Create an S3 bucket for storing Terraform state.
2ï¸âƒ£ Create a DynamoDB table for state locking.
3ï¸âƒ£ Define backend in terraform code:

hcl
Copy
Edit
terraform {
  backend "s3" {
    bucket         = "my-terraform-state-bucket"
    key            = "terraform.tfstate"
    region         = "us-east-1"
    dynamodb_table = "terraform-lock"
  }
}
âœ… This ensures the Terraform state is stored safely, and DynamoDB prevents multiple users from modifying it simultaneously (state locking).

